The second book traces the history of the west-Saxon empire through the line of Anglo- Saxon and Anglo-Danish sovereigns, to the death of Harold, and the arrival of the Nor- mans.

The third book is devoted to the reign of William the First.

The fourth and fifth books bring the history down to the year 1120. In the fourth book there is also a very interesting account of the first Crusade, with vivid sketches os the principal leaders therein engaged.
